{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"When a required key is absent from both the file and the environment, the error message names the missing key by its exact config path (e.g., `database.host`).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is the handoff between file loading, env override merge, and schema validation/error formatting. A unit test of only the validator could miss bugs in merge order or key-path propagation.","test_description":"Run the real config loader against a temp config file missing `database.host`, with `TOOL_DATABASE_HOST` unset. Assert startup fails and stderr/error text includes the exact missing path `database.host`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the environment variable `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` is set, the loader resolves the config file path relative to that directory rather than `~/.config`.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is specifically about module interaction between environment-variable path resolution and file loading. A pure unit path test can miss that the loader still opens the old default path.","test_description":"Create two temp config roots: one at a fake home `~/.config/tool/config.yaml` and one at `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/tool/config.yaml` with distinguishable values. Set `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` and run the real loader. Assert loaded values come from the XDG path.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When an environment variable with the `TOOL_` prefix conflicts with a key in the config file, the environment variable value is used.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real failure appears at the merge boundary between parsed YAML config and parsed `TOOL_` env vars